      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Mixing St. John's wort with sertraline is a dangerous idea because St. John's wort is a potent inducer of liver enzymes that will drastically lower your sertraline levels, rendering the medication ineffective just when you need it most. Furthermore, combining these two substances significantly increases the risk of serotonin syndrome, a potentially life-threatening condition characterized by confusion, rapid heart rate, and high body temperature. You should immediately stop considering this combination and consult your prescribing physician before taking any new supplements during your finals.",
